<TITLE> BCB Academy suffer another defeat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 13 (bdnews24.com)  Hosts GP-BCB Academy suffered a massive 246-run defeat against the visiting Sri Lankan Development squad on the fourth and final day of the second four-day game in Chittagong on Wednesday. Chasing an uphill target of 438, GP-BCB Academy team ended their second innings on 191 all out after having resumed the final day on 62-1 at the Bir Shreshtha Shaheed Ruhul Amin Stadium. Nasiruddin Faruque added only 10 runs to his overnight score of 33 while his partner Sagir Hossain, starting on overnight one, fell for 39 and their departure triggered a slump in the face of superb bowling by M Suriwardana, who returned five for 43. Lower order batsman Farhad Hossain chipped in with 24 runs, but could not avert the second successive defeat for the hosts. The Sri Lankan Development squad posted a massive 423 in the first innings before restricted the hosts to 164, and the visitors did not enforce the follow-on. They set GP-BCB Academy side to chase 346 to win the match after declaring their second innings on 178-9 on the third day on Tuesday. The GP-BCB National Cricket Academy lost the first four-day match by nine wickets. bd
